cs.FL, cs.CC, cs.LO, cs.CR, cs.DS 

The paper deals with encodings in language theory and computability theory, which are closely related to formal languages and automata. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory). The paper also discusses the power of models of computation, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The construction of encodings and their properties involve set theory and logic, which could place the paper in cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also mentions finite-state automata, which are a fundamental data structure in computer science, and could indicate that it belongs to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses the recognizability of sets of natural numbers, which could suggest that it belongs to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
